nts1.d:
Berlin techno aficionado Prosumer lays it out for all the wannabes. A harmonious lecture in house and soul, Prosumer’s here to share.
From the host: "Set recorded at Standard Time Toronto in 2023"

nts1.n: Self Soothe w/ Margeaux - devotional special
nts1.d: Settle in for weekly shows from Margeaux aka @marg.mp3, soothing with an hour of selections, offering an eclectic range of sounds old and new.
Japanese DJ Yuka Mizuhara joins us for an hour every month, selecting the most feel good classic house and disco. Dig!

An overview of the cult Japanese label series, Digital Trip. Including the subtitle "Fantasy Series", Digital trip was a celebration of the synthesizer. Across the labels output, well known anime and film soundtracks were re-interpreted with electronic arrangements, producing a fascinating, multi-genre array of results, from proto-ambient, to synth-pop, to a digitised take on Italian library music.

Veteran NTS host Hampus brings you Doing Time: a genre-agnostic monthly trip through quality records from around the world’s past and present, featuring regular appearances from musical friends and family.
A fresh take on dubstep from London producer Truant.

"Having freshly touched down in Bristol for the day, Introspekt comes through with an all vinyl mix centered around 2nd wave Dubstep classics from the Bristol scene. Loads of heavy dubwise steppers inbound!"
2 hour bi-monthly excursions into sound and dissonance. Music label with John T. Gast. Regular guest selections from friends and affiliates.
Danish label Posh Isolation join us for an hour a month.
An hour where anything goes, leaning toward the hazy and the off-kilter, courtesy of Melbourne's Bridget Small.

Diving into the catalogues of Gene and Dean Ween.
Mix by Brian Coney.

nts2.n: Immanentizing the Eschaton w/ Mark Leckey
nts2.d:
Contemporary British AV artist, collagist, and NTS host Mark Leckey takes to the airwaves to play oddities from his collection. Everything from doo-wop to gabber.
From the host: "More of the holy and profane for 2026."

North London native and Hyperdub signee Loraine James is an electronic producer who effortlessly blends Electronica and IDM with whispers of jazz and ambience all wrapped up in the artists key avant-garde aesthetic and sensibility.

nts2.n: THE SHADOW CHANNEL MONTAGE W/ SPELLCASTER
nts2.d: A mix montaging music from the third and final spellcaster album ‘the shadow channel’ and its expanded universe in excerpts from live recordings of the spellchestra from the recent year. ‘the shadow channel’ is the symbolic transition rite from spellcaster to spellchestra and the origin story of the operatic roleplaying ensemble.
Lamin Fofana is an artist living in New York City.

International touring DJs, record label, and longstanding Glaswegian party was founded by Jonnie Wilkes (JG Wilkes) & Keith McIvor (JD Twitch) in Glasgow in 1997. Optimo now exists as the solo project of JG Wilkes since the tragic and untimely passing of JD Twitch in September 2025. The Optimo (Espacio) NTS show, now in it's 10th year, exhibits a unique disregard for genres and musical restrictions,  striking out into often head-messing territories - from the "sublime to the ridiculous" - oddball electronic, Post Punk rarities, 4th World, EBM, Dub, Techno, Synth Pop, and bags of new unreleased gold.

nts2.n: THE LUNACY OF FLOWERS W/ DAVE ID
nts2.d: Dave I.D takes us through industrial, and techno – melodic and dark. New and classic goth, his selection sets him apart from most, branching decades and scenes.
“Feelings of inhabiting a cloud” Mexico City-based duo select some newly treasured songs, including their latest single.
Brooklyn musician Nick Hakim takes over the NTS airwaves.

Los Hitters is the collective partnership of Joe Cristando (Couple Two T’ree) and Rene Lopez (Suavecito Souldies). A collaboration that links the two from Brooklyn, NY to Oakland, CA. Their mixes focus on soul sounds comprised of their vinyl collection.

nts2.n: FUSION BATCHES W/ DJ MORSE CODE
nts2.d:
DJ / Producer Morse Code brings us a monthly all vinyl mix of jazz-funk, jazz fusion, and rare groove in the tradition of his Fusion Batches mixes from the mid 00's, which championed dollar bin heat as well as the rares, all in the name of the hunt for the best grooves!
From the host: "this episode contains a tribute to Michal Urbaniak as well as some tunes from Phil Upchurch, two luminaries of the jazz-funk world who recently passed on.  It also features some tunes I found while digging in The Bay over the holiday break.  Bless up for the new year, all the best to you!"

nts2.n: El Sabor De La Ciudad w/ REGAL86 (R)
nts2.d: Monterrey-born club producer extraordinaire Regal86 presents 'El Sabor de la Ciudad', or 'The Taste of The City' laying out the sounds that have inspired him and his regular guests, past and present.

Lex Records artist Boom Bip scrapes beneath the surface of the status quo by loosely basing his mixes on electronics and the new waves they produce.
From the host: "Soul, Groove and Chill Funk"

subtle.d: Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

subtle.n: Out of Phase With Sam Ling

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

subtle.d:
Midlands born, London based producer and DJ influenced by UK funky, broken techno, garage and early dubstep. 

Has released on Keysound recordings, RKS, eatmybeat, ec2a, Durkle Disco and Dimsum records

2Step Selects is a monthly show hosted by the Choki Biki Records crew. Founded in Dublin, Ireland, CBR consists of DJ Sharpson, 2step.png, Frame Shift, and MICK. The show consists of an all round breaks, electro, ukg and jungle hour, followed by an Irish showcase, demonstrating all the best Ireland has to offer collective/party/Dj & Producer wise!

dublab.n: Echo Park Film Center - Optical Track

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
Peak Oil records presents ‘tipping point’; a monthly journey through the record collections of brian and brion. Leaving no good genre unturned, enjoy two hours of esoterica, conversation and guests.
